posts.description: 10 new wars that could be unleashed as a result of the one against ISIS - The Washington Post
posts.extended: The borders of the Islamic State's "caliphate" are shrinking fast. The groupâ€™s strongholds in Iraq and Syria are collapsing one by one. The U.S.-led war has reached a point where questions are being raised about what comes next. So far, the answer seems likely to be: more war.
